<title>FINLAND: Finnish govt agrees on cen bank independence - radio.</title>
<headline>Finnish govt agrees on cen bank independence - radio.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Finnish government agreed on Thursday to revise the central bank laws and grant the bank independence from political influence in line with requirements for Economic and Monetary Union (EMU), Finnish radio news said.</p>
<p>Government officials familiar with the matter were not immediately available for comment and no further details were available. The radio said the proposal would strip the Bank of Finland board of parliamentary supervisors of its authority in foreign exchange decision-making, and grant the central bank's board of management full powers over exchange rate policy. @</p>
<p>The supervisors -- nine MPs appointed by parliamentary groups in proportion to party representation in the single-chamber legislature -- have repeatedly said they oppose such a transfer of powers.</p>
<p>--Peter Starck, Helsinki Newsroom  +358 - 9 - 680 50 245</p>
